{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7zBeEdazc2V39Gb7KP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Both tests pass, including the pre-existing cache test.\n\n**What was wrong:** In `src/userService.js`, the cache key was `users:${opts.team}` — it ignored `opts.includeArchived`. So when any caller requested a team *with* archived users, that result got cached for 60s and served to the people picker's *without-archived* request for the same team. The picker never asked for archived users; it just got a stale cache entry populated by a different call. The TTL is why \"refreshing after a minute clears it\" — the entry expires and the picker's own request repopulates it correctly.\n\n**The fix:** Include `includeArchived` in the cache key (`users:${opts.team}:${opts.includeArchived ? 1 : 0}`) so the archived and non-archived variants get separate cache entries and never cross-contaminate.\n\nThe repro test in `test/userService.test.js` stays as the regression guard."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":321,"cache_read_input_tokens":25800,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":321},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d4e60c-1bc0-404e-9e04-dd8f14ffb39b","uuid":"4c7febfd-f87f-4e69-beb8-7ef7eab2190c","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:47:41.188Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7zAQKpbDJD1BjxsXbW"}
